OL,6,F"Those who carry them often don't
OL,7,Fappreciate this impact, and don't
OL,8,Fappreciate that by carrying a knife,
OL,9,Fthey are far more likely to become a
OL,10,Fvictim of knife crime themselves.
OL,12,F"It is a priority of Sussex Police to
OL,13,Ftackle knife crime and serious
OL,14,Fviolence, to educate people about
OL,15,Fknife safety, and to work with
OL,16,Fpartners to reduce knife crime and
OL,17,Ffear of knife crime to keep our
OL,18,Fcommunities safe."
